6.10 pm Usually a score as big as this needs a top-order batsman to make most of the running. And Quinton de Kock was the man to do it for South Africa. He eased past some early jitters with his footwork, was willing to work for his runs and take advantage of the bad balls. A century he will remember for a while, and cherish if his team wins. But there was another man who deserves equal plaudits, one who has been under an intense scanner. Farhaan Behardien does not look like a man who can score 63 off 41, but he showed off some sparkling strokes, especially off the back foot to put a pretty handy target. Join us in about half an hour to see the Australian chase

Kamran: "aaand Behardien's batting average goes below Parnell's once again. But he's played a very crucial innings."
